tekken-coach
============

This product includes frame-data derived from third-party community sources. The data is
used with attribution; no third-party application *code* is vendored (see THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES
for the code/data split).

Frame data (assets/framedata/)
------------------------------
Frame-data snapshots under `assets/framedata/` are ingested (via `fetch-framedata`) from the
Wavu-derived CSV files published by the `pbruvoll/tekkendocs` repository, which is the source
behind tekkendocs.com. The underlying frame data originates from the Tekken community, notably:

  - tekkendocs.com
  - rbnorway.org

Each snapshot's `manifest.json` records the exact pinned upstream commit SHA and per-character
source checksums, so every snapshot is reproducible and traceable to its source.

The `pbruvoll/tekkendocs` *application code* is restrictively licensed and is NOT used or
vendored here — only the published *data* is ingested, with the attribution above. See docs/05
§3.1 for the data-vs-code licensing split.

Punisher profiles (assets/punishers/)
--------------------------------------
The curated per-character punisher profiles under `assets/punishers/` are frame-number facts
(startup, notation, launch property) hand-curated for the scoped matchups. Specific block-punish
recommendations are cross-checked against the same community sources plus:

  - okizeme.gg
  - wavu.wiki

These are numeric facts, not vendored code. See docs/05 §3.1 / §4.1 for the sourcing posture.
